   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">File transfer is used both to update the firmware and to download
logs. There are two different protocols that can be used with different
security options: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">File transfer protocol (FTP): With FTP the information is transferred
as plain text. Use SCP for increased security.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Secure copy protocol (SCP): With SCP the information is encrypted.
SCP is automatically used when the SSH protocol is enabled and configured
and the FTP protocol is disabled.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
